1+0000","customfield_12312335":null,"customfield_12312336":null,"status":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"Consider the following two scenarios\n1)   With permissions ON, start cluster as user A, create a file as user A, chmod 770 file as user A, access file as user B(using 'get' command) \nThe expected behavior would be that user B should be able to access the file since user A and user B are in the same group. But this is not happening. Instead the following error message is displayed \"get: Permission denied\"\n\n2)  With permissions ON, start cluster as user A, create a file as user A, chmod 700 file as user A, shut down dfs and turn permissions OFF and start up dfs, access file as user B(using 'get')\nThe expected behavior would be that user B should be able to access the file since permissions is turned OFF. But this is not happening. Instead the following error message is displayed \"get: Permission denied\"","customfield_10010":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_12312026":null,"customfield_12312023":null,"customfield_12310320":null,"customfield_12312024":null,"customfield_12312340":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"customfield_12312341":null,"customfield_12312220":null,"customfield_12312022":null,"customfield_12310921":null,"customfield_12310920":"104416","customfield_12312823":null,"summary":"Unable to access a file by a different user in the same group when permissions is set to 770 or when permissions is turned OFF","creator":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"subtasks":[],"customfield_12310291":null,"reporter":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"customfield_12310290":null,"aggregateprogress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"customfield_12311024":null,"environment":null,"customfield_12313520":null,"customfield_12311020":null,"duedate":null,"customfield_12310250":null,"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"comment":{"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12405343/comment/12636198","id":"12636198","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hairong","name":"hairong","key":"hairong","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Hairong Kuang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"I tried both scenarios. All worked. Did the error message you saw come from the local file system? Please try using \"cat\" instead of \"get\".","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hairong","name":"hairong","key":"hairong","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Hairong Kuang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2008-10-01T22:04:37.074+0000","updated":"2008-10-01T22:04:37.074+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12405343/comment/12637115","id":"12637115","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"\"cat\" definitely works but since the permissions is set to 770 in case 1 and permissions is turned OFF in case 2, a user in the same group should be able to read, write and execute the file. So in that case, shouldn't \"get \" also be supported? Why is \"get\"not supported in the above two cases?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2008-10-06T15:15:36.629+0000","updated":"2008-10-06T15:15:36.629+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12405343/comment/12637141","id":"12637141","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hairong","name":"hairong","key":"hairong","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Hairong Kuang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Get writes the dfs file to your local disk. Could you please check if the user has the permission to write to the local disk in both scenarios?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hairong","name":"hairong","key":"hairong","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Hairong Kuang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2008-10-06T17:09:40.589+0000","updated":"2008-10-06T17:09:40.589+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12405343/comment/12637393","id":"12637393","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"The user did not have permission to write to the local disk in both scenarios. Thats the reason why it was unable to \"get:\" the file. Thanks Hairong. \nResolving this issue.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rramya","name":"rramya","key":"rramya","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Ramya Sunil","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2008-10-07T06:27:45.682+0000","updated":"2008-10-07T06:27:45.682+0000"}],"maxResults":4,"total":4,"startAt":0},"votes":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/HADOOP-4299/votes","votes":0,"hasVoted":false},"worklog":{"startAt":0,"maxResults":20,"total":0,"worklogs":[]},"customfield_12311820":"0|i0i85r:"}}